doctype html
head
  meta(name='viewport' content='width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0, user-scalable=no')
  meta(charset='utf-8')
  script(type='text/javascript' src='../icao-atc-phraseology-tts.js')
  style.
  
    joeherwig-atc-phraseology-tts {
      width: 100%;
    }
    code {
      background: #9999995a;
      padding: 0.25em;
    }
    div > code {
      display: block;
      overflow: auto;
      counter-reset: line;
      white-space: pre;
    }
    div > code p{
      counter-increment: line;
      margin: 0px;
      color: grey;
    }
    div > code p:before{
      content: counter(line);
      margin: 0 1em 0 1em;
      color: grey;
    }
    div > code p.focus {
      color: black;
    }

    .caution {
      background: #ffa5005e;
      border: 0px solid transparent;
      border-left: 3px solid #666666;
      font-style: italic;
      color: #333333;
      page-break-inside: avoid;
      text-align: left;
      margin-bottom: 1.6em;
      max-width: 100%;
      overflow: auto;
      padding: 1em 1.5em;
      display: block;
      word-wrap: break-word;
    }

    .caution::before {
      content: "⚠️";
      font-style: normal;
      margin-right: 0.5em;
      display: block;
      float: left;
      font-size: 2em;
    }
body
  h1 Include it 
  by simply adding the js file in your website like 

  div 
    code
      | &lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;
      | &lt;html&gt;
      |   &lt;head&gt;
      |    ...
      |
      b
        |     &lt;script type="text/javascript" src="https://gitlab.com/joeherwig/joeherwig-webcomponents/-/raw/master/webcomponents/joeherwig-flightboard.js"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;
  p in your webpage..
  p Then use it where you want to add your ICAO content like that:
  div
    code
      |   ...
      |   &lt;body&gt;
      |     ...
      b
        |   &lt;joeherwig-atc-phraseology&gt;
        |     ...
        |     &lt;div class="acft"&gt;Stuttgart Delivery, DLH22G, Position 12, Information K, request Startup and clearance to Zürich.&lt;/div&gt;
        |     &lt;div class="atc"&gt;DLH22G, good morning, say again your Position.&lt;/div&gt;
        |     ...
        |     &lt;div class="acft"&gt;DLH22G, we're on Position 12.&lt;/div&gt;
        |     &lt;div class="atc"&gt;DLH22G, cleared to Munich via Rotweil 5B Departure. Climb Altitude 5000ft.&lt;/div&gt;
        |   &lt;/joeherwig-atc-phraseology&gt;
        |
      |     ...
      |     
  p of course you can also structure your aeronautical radio documentation with headlines, paragraphs, lists, figures and images etc.
  p we just work with divs of classes 
    code atc
    |  and 
    code acft
    | .

